          "tpd_sd_q": 18
        },
        "behavior": "; 7474 — two independent positive-edge D flip-flops with async set and reset.\n;\n; Equations are physical-level GALasm: '/' is the complement operator and a\n; signal name is this file's pin name with any active-low '/' prefix dropped\n; (pin /1SD is GAL signal 1SD, so '/1SD' means \"pin /1SD is LOW\" = set\n; asserted). Derived from the function tables (datasheet Tables 3 and 4).\n;\n; Each flip-flop has its OWN clock, so there is no global clock: key. Instead\n; each registered output carries the GAL20RA10 extended-dialect suffixes\n; (FR-079a): .CLK names its clock pin, .APRST its async set, .ARST its async\n; reset. Set/reset are level-sensitive and override the clock (async).\n;\n; Complementary outputs: the datasheet's Q-bar pins cannot be named '/1Q'/'/2Q'\n; (the '/' strips to the same signal as 1Q/2Q and would collide), so they are\n; named 1QB/2QB and derived as the inverse of the Q net (one unit-delay later,\n; invisible at human pacing). NOTE: the datasheet's not-recommended state\n; SD=RD=LOW (both asserted, where the real part drives BOTH outputs HIGH) is\n; not modeled faithfully — reset dominates here and the derived complement\n; keeps Q and Q-bar opposite.\n1Q.R = 1D\n1Q.CLK = 1CP\n1Q.APRST = /1SD\n1Q.ARST = /1RD\n1QB = /1Q\n2Q.R = 2D\n2Q.CLK = 2CP\n2Q.APRST = /2SD\n2Q.ARST = /2RD\n2QB = /2Q\n",
        "description": "dual D-type flip-flop with set and reset, positive edge-triggered",
        "datasheet": {
          "vendor": "Nexperia",
          "title": "74HC74; 74HCT74 Dual D-type flip-flop with set and reset; positive edge-trigger",
          "rev": "Rev. 9, 2 April 2024",
          "url": "https://assets.nexperia.com/documents/data-sheet/74HC_HCT74.pdf"
        },
